Justice Inyang Ekwo of the Federal High Court sitting in Abuja, on Wednesday granted permission to former Imo state Governor, Anayo Rochas Okorocha to travel to the United States of America for medical attention. Okorocha is present, the Senator representing Imo West in the Senate. Subsequently, Justice Ekwo ordered the Registrar of the Court to release the travelling passport of the former governor to him to enable him to embark on the medical trip. The order sequel an application by Ola Olanipekun SAN, who notified the court that his client has been having health challenges in recent times. Olanipekun told the court that Okorocha will not abuse the order and will return to the country for his trial as soon as his medical appointment abroad elapses. Though Chile Okoroma, counsel representing the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission had wanted to oppose the request, however, he made a u-turn as Justice Ekwo stated that the request would be granted with a caveat by the court. The court held that should Okorocha refuse to return and face his trial, a bench warrant of arrest would be issued against him and consequently declared wanted. However, Justice Ekwo ordered Okorocha to return his international passport to the Court Registrar not later than three days of his return to the country. Meanwhile, the court has fixed November 7, for his trial in the money laundering criminal charges brought against him by the Federal Government.